line_1: The sober trader at a tatter'd cloak,
line_2: Wakes from his dream, and labours for a joke;

line_1: Either to honour band and cloak,
line_2: Did never me as yet provoke,

line_1: Either to honour band and cloak,
line_2: Or deck my hat with leaves of oak.

line_1: WHEN dark oblivion in her sable cloak
line_2: And their high deeds submitting to the stroke
